First Avenue (across view from right to left and obscured by roof tops) north from E. 23rd Street (extreme right) showing a general view northeastward from a loft structure at the S.E. corner of Second Avenue and E. 22nd Street. Silhouetted against the Bellevue Hospital Buildings is the New York Life Insurance Co. printing plant building at the S.W. corner of First Avenue and E. 25th Street. The J.J. Little and Ives Co. printing plant and book bindery is on the north side of E. 24th Street east of First Avenue and near the East River.

September 3, 1929.
Views 1 and 2

P.L. Sperr
